					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drarmstrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(420092); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=420092&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250883" alt="DrArmstrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=420092)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drarmstrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(420092); return false;" >DrArmstrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1478281895 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Nov 2016 17:51</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2684403">
									

<p>Cryptic Dream Sequences have the potential, in my opinion, to be quite bad. I've seen and read many that were either too cryptic and weird to mean anything to the audience, and thus failed to foreshadow anything as most people lost interest, or were too heavy-handed and obvious, ruining any attempts at suspense in the future.</p>
<p>This was fucking great, as it hit a balance between expanding on the story and dropping some fresh baked WTF on us. SCP-001/humanity's connection to &quot;hands&quot; and the mover behind 001 being love are especially compelling.</p>
<p>+1</p>

							</div>

								
					
